title: Expect lots of last-minute travel bookings to Orlando for Labor Day weekend
text:
Seattle Washington, D.C. Meanwhile, internationally, Americans are taking advantage of favorable currency exchange rates by cashing in on hotel deals across Europe. Foreign markets seeing a rise in demand include Barcelona, Spain, where average daily hotel rates in U.S. dollars are down more than 20 percent; and Florence, Italy, where average daily rates are down more than 5 percent. Other popular international destinations for Labor Day 2015 include Paris, London and Rome. Tourism is the Central Florida region's largest economic engine and feeds a $60 billion tourism industry. Last year, Orlando was the most-visited destination in the U.S., welcoming more than 62 million visitors who booked room nights at area hotels, ate at local restaurants and contributed other dollars to the local economy.
